  "text": "In addition, the actin perturbing binary toxin (CDT) was found as an additional toxin in 4-12% of toxigenic C. difficile. This additional toxin is composed of two independent components, a catalytic domain (CDTа) and a binding domain (CDTβ) [CITATION_1] . This toxin has been reported to be independently associated with recurrent CDI [CITATION_2] .",
